Help [=[

matrix.slice(m [, first] [, last] [, step])
-------------------------------------------

Returns a _section_ of matrix `m` that is a slice in the first dimension of
`m` starting at `first` (defaults to 1), ending at `last` (defaults to
`#m`), and alternating by `step` (defaults to 1) positions. The returned
section is a _reference_ to `m`.

A shortcut for `matrix.slice(m, first, last, step)` is `m(first, last, step)`.

__See also__: `matrix.section`
]=]
